# Component Development Guidelines

## Component Structure

- All components should be placed in the appropriate directory under [registry/domino/](mdc:registry/domino/)
- Base UI components go in [registry/domino/ui/](mdc:registry/domino/ui/)
- Complex component blocks go in [registry/domino/blocks/](mdc:registry/domino/blocks/)
- Shared hooks go in [registry/domino/hooks/](mdc:registry/domino/hooks/)

## Component Registry

- Each component must have a corresponding JSON file in [registry.json](mdc:registry.json)

## shadcn/ui Integration

- Use the existing UI components from [registry/domino/ui/](mdc:registry/domino/ui/)
- Follow the shadcn/ui design patterns and component API
- Check [components.json](mdc:components.json) for configuration details

## TypeScript Best Practices

- Use proper TypeScript types for all props and state
- Export component types for reuse
- Use React.FC or proper function component typing
- Implement proper prop interfaces

## File Organization

- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Use descriptive file names that match component names
- Group related components in subdirectories when needed
- Export components as default exports for registry compatibility
